Creating a simplified version of the Piano Tiles game as a web app can be achieved with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Below is a single HTML file containing everything you need to create a UI clone of the Piano Tiles game that plays "Ampyx - Lmao." The game will feature basic functionality where colored tiles fall from the top, and the user must click on them as they reach the bottom.

Here's the code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Piano Tiles Clone</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #222;
            color: white;
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
        }
        #gameContainer {
            position: relative;
            width: 300px;
            height: 600px;
            overflow: hidden;
            border: 4px solid #fff;
        }
        .tile {
            position: absolute;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #f00;
            border: 1px solid #000;
            transition: background-color 0.1s;
        }
        .tile.active {
            background-color: #0f0;
        }
        #score {
            position: absolute;
            top: 10px;
            left: 10px;
            font-size: 24px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="gameContainer">
        <div id="score">Score: 0</div>
    </div>
    <audio id="music" src="https://www.bensound.com/bensound-ukulele.mp3" autoplay loop></audio> <!-- Replace this with actual URL of copyright-free music -->
    <script>
        const gameContainer = document.getElementById('gameContainer');
        const scoreDisplay = document.getElementById('score');
        let score = 0;
        let tileSpeed = 1000; // milliseconds
        let gameInterval;

        function createTile() {
            const tile = document.createElement('div');
            tile.classList.add('tile');
            gameContainer.appendChild(tile);
            const randomColor = '#' + Math.floor(Math.random()*16777215).toString(16);
            tile.style.backgroundColor = randomColor;

            let tilePosition = 0;
            const fall = () => {
                tilePosition += 5; // speed of tiles falling
                tile.style.top = tilePosition + 'px';

                if (tilePosition > gameContainer.clientHeight) {
                    clearInterval(tileInterval);
                    gameContainer.removeChild(tile);
                    endGame();
                }
            };

            const tileInterval = setInterval(fall, 20);
            tile.addEventListener('click', () => {
                if (tile.classList.contains('active')) {
                    score++;
                    scoreDisplay.innerText = 'Score: ' + score;
                    clearInterval(tileInterval);
                    gameContainer.removeChild(tile);
                }
            });

            setTimeout(() => {
                if (gameContainer.contains(tile)) {
                    tile.classList.add('active');
                }
            }, tileSpeed - 200); // time before changing to active
        }

        function endGame() {
            clearInterval(gameInterval);
            alert('Game Over! Your score: ' + score);
            location.reload(); // reload the game
        }

        gameInterval = setInterval(createTile, tileSpeed);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use This Code:
1. Copy the above code into a text editor (such as Notepad, Visual Studio Code, etc.).
2. Save the file with a `.html` extension, for example, `piano_tiles_clone.html`.
3. Open the saved file in a web browser.

### Notes:
- The audio element uses a placeholder URL; you need to replace it with an actual URL of "Ampyx - Lmao" available on platforms providing copyright-free music.
- This is a basic implementation and can be improved by adding features like increasing difficulty, multiple levels, and better graphics.
- The game logic is simplistic; consider enhancing it for a better user experience.

Certainly! Below is an updated version of the Piano Tiles clone. This new version includes 7 lanes (for a total of 8), as well as instructions on how to play. The instructions are displayed at the beginning and can be dismissed by clicking a button.

Here’s the complete code for the web app:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Piano Tiles Clone</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            flex-direction: column;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #222;
            color: white;
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        #gameContainer {
            position: relative;
            width: 400px; /* Increased width for more lanes */
            height: 600px;
            overflow: hidden;
            border: 4px solid #fff;
        }
        .tile {
            position: absolute;
            width: 50px; /* Width of each tile */
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #f00;
            border: 1px solid #000;
            transition: background-color 0.1s;
        }
        .tile.active {
            background-color: #0f0;
        }
        #score {
            position: absolute;
            top: 10px;
            left: 10px;
            font-size: 24px;
        }
        #instructions {
            position: absolute;
            top: 50%;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
            border: 2px solid #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            display: none;
        }
        #instructions button {
            margin-top: 10px;
            padding: 5px 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="instructions">
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <p>Click on the green tiles as they fall!</p>
        <p>Avoid missing any tiles!</p>
        <button onclick="startGame()">Start Game</button>
    </div>
    <div id="gameContainer">
        <div id="score">Score: 0</div>
    </div>
    <audio id="music" src="https://www.bensound.com/bensound-ukulele.mp3" autoplay loop></audio> <!-- Replace with actual URL of copyright-free music -->
    <script>
        const gameContainer = document.getElementById('gameContainer');
        const scoreDisplay = document.getElementById('score');
        const instructions = document.getElementById('instructions');
        let score = 0;
        let tileSpeed = 1000; // milliseconds
        let gameInterval;

        function showInstructions() {
            instructions.style.display = 'block';
        }

        function startGame() {
            instructions.style.display = 'none';
            gameInterval = setInterval(createTile, tileSpeed);
        }

        function createTile() {
            const tile = document.createElement('div');
            tile.classList.add('tile');

            // Randomly select a lane (0 to 7 for 8 lanes)
            const lane = Math.floor(Math.random() * 8) * 50; // Each tile is 50px wide
            tile.style.left = lane + 'px';
            gameContainer.appendChild(tile);

            const randomColor = '#' + Math.floor(Math.random() * 16777215).toString(16);
            tile.style.backgroundColor = randomColor;

            let tilePosition = 0;
            const fall = () => {
                tilePosition += 5; // speed of tiles falling
                tile.style.top = tilePosition + 'px';

                if (tilePosition > gameContainer.clientHeight) {
                    clearInterval(tileInterval);
                    gameContainer.removeChild(tile);
                    endGame();
                }
            };

            const tileInterval = setInterval(fall, 20);
            tile.addEventListener('click', () => {
                if (tile.classList.contains('active') || true) { // Always considers the tile active in this simple version
                    score++;
                    scoreDisplay.innerText = 'Score: ' + score;
                    clearInterval(tileInterval);
                    gameContainer.removeChild(tile);
                }
            });

            setTimeout(() => {
                if (gameContainer.contains(tile)) {
                    tile.classList.add('active');
                }
            }, tileSpeed - 200); // time before changing to active
        }

        function endGame() {
            clearInterval(gameInterval);
            alert('Game Over! Your score: ' + score);
            location.reload(); // reload the game
        }

        // Show instructions when the page loads
        window.onload = showInstructions;
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use This Code:
1. Copy the above code into a text editor (such as Notepad, Visual Studio Code, etc.).
2. Save the file with a `.html` extension, for example, `piano_tiles_clone.html`.
3. Open the saved file in a web browser.

### New Features:
- **8 Lanes**: The game now has 8 lanes for tiles to fall into, allowing for more challenging gameplay.
- **Instructions**: A set of instructions appears when the game starts, explaining how to play. Users can dismiss the instructions by clicking the "Start Game" button.

### Customize Further:
- Remember to replace the audio source URL with the actual URL of the desired copyright-free music.
- You can enhance the game further by introducing features like scoreboards, different levels of speed, or even animations.

